// Basic
 - (try,catch,finally) used for exception handling
 - Helps to handle error in your program without crashing

// try,catch,finally
 (try)
    Block contains the logic of the code, If it contains error it will
    pass to catch block

 (catch)
    It will execute only when the try block contain the error

 (finally)
    This block runs always, no matter what.
    It runs when:
      ✔ no error
      ✔ error happened
      ✔ even if you use return inside try/catch
    Note - used for logging, disposing the unmanaged resourse

